You can try to set the `controls` property to `false`, but it might hide some controls you didn&#39;t want to.

If your url is for example a Vimeo url, you can try to do something like this:

    &lt;ReactPlayer
       url=&#39;http://vimeo.com/...&#39;
       vimeoConfig={{ iframeParams: { fullscreen: 0 } }}
    /&gt;

If it is a youtube url try this:

    &lt;ReactPlayer
        url=&#39;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mFJZ0HaYYB8&#39;
        config={{
            youtube: {
                 playerVars: { modestbranding: 1 }
            }
        }}
    /&gt;

Have a look on [this][1] page, it might help as well, or in the [official component page][2] under the **Config prop** section :)


  [1]: https://github.com/CookPete/react-player/issues/560
  [2]: https://www.npmjs.com/package/react-player

